      "content": "# Run for X Seconds\n\nLet's make the device that turns on the LED for three seconds when you press the button.\n\nThe `delay` node help us with this task. Generally, this node is used to postpone the pulse for some time, but when `delay` node is activated it also outputs True value on the `ACT` pin. This additional feature of the `delay` node helps us to get rid of the pattern `flip-flop`+`delay` nodes.\n\nSo it's what we need.\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. Add `button` node and bind `PORT` pin.\n\n2. Link it with the `SET` pin of the `delay` node.\n\n3. Change the `T` value to 3.\n\n4. Upload the program and press the button.\n\n## Additional Excercise\n\nCombine few `delay` nodes by chaining `DONE` and `SET` pins to get a custom pattern of blinking LED. Use the `or` node to take some of the `ACT`ing delays.",
